{"id":720,"date":"2021-08-12T04:19:48","date_gmt":"2021-08-12T04:19:48","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/taipinginstitute.com\/?page_id=720"},"modified":"2024-02-11T08:12:28","modified_gmt":"2024-02-11T08:12:28","slug":"bagua-hunyuan-qigong-%e5%a4%aa%e4%b9%99%e5%85%ab%e5%8d%a6%e6%b7%b7%e5%85%83%e9%a4%8a%e7%94%9f%e5%8a%9f-2","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"http:\/\/taipinginstitute.com\/bagua-hunyuan-qigong-%e5%a4%aa%e4%b9%99%e5%85%ab%e5%8d%a6%e6%b7%b7%e5%85%83%e9%a4%8a%e7%94%9f%e5%8a%9f-2\/","title":{"rendered":"Bagua Hunyuan Qigong | \u592a\u4e59\u516b\u5366\u6df7\u5143\u990a\u751f\u529f"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>The Taiyi Bagua Hunyuan Yangsheng Gong was developed by our Grandmaster Lu Zijian (1893-2012) who lived almost 120 years. He attributed his longevity to the daily practice of this particular Qigong method which he developed by integrating the essence of Daoist cultivation practices that he studied throughout his life from the Wudang and Bagua Schools of Daoism\/martial arts. There are two parts to the practice of Taiyi Gong which includes the Internal Alchemy (Qing, Qi, Shen Transformation) and the Specific Yangsheng routine.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Yangsheng Gong\u00a0<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"alignright size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"582\" height=\"311\" src=\"http:\/\/taipinginstitute.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/baguayangsheng2.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1929\" style=\"width:604px;height:auto\" srcset=\"http:\/\/taipinginstitute.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/baguayangsheng2.jpg 582w, http:\/\/taipinginstitute.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/baguayangsheng2-300x160.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 582px) 100vw, 582px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>&nbsp;Wuji Gong Fa (\u65e0\u6781\u529f\u6cd5 Primordial Gong)<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>&nbsp;Taiji Zhuanbi (\u592a\u6781\u8f6c\u81c2 Taiji Turning Arms)<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>&nbsp;Caiqi Paifei (\u91c7\u6c14\u6392\u5e9f Pluck the air and eliminate toxins)<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>&nbsp;Shuanghuan Taoyue (\u53cc\u73af\u5957\u6708 Pair of Rings covering the moon)<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>&nbsp;Zuoyou Rouqiu (\u5de6\u53f3\u62b1\u7403 Left and Right Embrace the Soft Ball)<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>&nbsp;Zuoma Tuizhang (\u5750\u9a6c\u63a8\u638c Horse Riding Step Push Palms)<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>&nbsp;Zuoma Wanzhang (\u5750\u9a6c\u8155\u638c Horse Riding Turn the wrists)<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>&nbsp;Shuanglong Xizhu (\u53cc\u9f99\u620f\u73e0 Twin Dragons Play with the Pearls)<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>&nbsp;Zuoma Tigang (\u5750\u9a6c\u63d0\u809b Horse Riding Lift the Gang)<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>&nbsp;Heixiong Cabei (\u9ed1\u718a\u64e6\u80cc Black Bear rubs its back )<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>&nbsp;Zuoma Guanyue (\u5750\u9a6c\u89c2\u6708 Sit in Horse and gaze at the moon)<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>&nbsp;Kaihe Jiqiu (\u5f00\u5408\u6324\u7403 Open and close squeezing the ball)<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>&nbsp;Faqi Yunmu (\u53d1\u6c14\u8fd0\u76ee Release Qi towards the eyes)<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>&nbsp;Neiqi Guiding (\u5185\u6c14\u8d35\u9876 Internal Qi linked to the peak)<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>&nbsp;Heche Douzhuan (\u6cb3\u8f66\u6597\u8f6c River boat turning and shaking vigorously)&nbsp;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>The Taiyi Bagua Hunyuan Yangsheng Gong was developed by our Grandmaster Lu Zijian (1893-2012) who lived almost 120 years. He attributed his longevity to the daily practice of this particular Qigong method which he developed by integrating the essence of Daoist cultivation practices that he studied throughout his life from the Wudang and Bagua Schools [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":{"pgc_sgb_lightbox_settings":"","footnotes":""},"_links":{"self":[{"href":"http:\/\/taipinginstitute.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/720"}],"collection":[{"href":"http:\/\/taipinginstitute.com\/wp-json\/wp